  "text": "The xDS DiscoveryResponse flow through Envoy's C++ codebase proceeds as follows:\n\n1. **gRPC Stream Handler** (`grpc_stream.h`): `GrpcStream::onReceiveMessage()` is the entry point \u2014 it implements `Grpc::AsyncStreamCallbacks` and calls `callbacks_->onDiscoveryResponse()` when a message arrives from the management server. `GrpcStreamInterface` defines the abstract interface. `GrpcMuxFailover` wraps two GrpcStreams (primary + failover) and proxies callbacks.\n\n2. **Response Routing & Validation** \u2014 two parallel implementations:\n   - **Legacy SotW** (`grpc_mux_impl.cc`): `GrpcMuxImpl::onDiscoveryResponse()` receives the message, checks type_url subscription state, decodes resources via `DecodedResourceImpl::fromResource()`, validates type_url consistency per-resource, filters heartbeats, and then calls `processDiscoveryResources()`. Config validators (`config_validators_->executeValidators()`) are also invoked here.\n   - **Delta** (`new_grpc_mux_impl.cc`): `NewGrpcMuxImpl::onDiscoveryResponse()` delegates to `DeltaSubscriptionState::handleResponse()` \u2192 `handleGoodResponse()` which validates for duplicate names and type_url mismatches.\n   - **xds_mux variants** (`xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc`): `GrpcMuxImpl::genericHandleResponse()` \u2192 `BaseSubscriptionState::handleResponse()` \u2192 either `SotwSubscriptionState::handleGoodResponse()` or `XdsMux::DeltaSubscriptionState::handleGoodResponse()`.\n\n3. **Resource Version Bookkeeping**:\n   - SotW: `GrpcMuxImpl::ApiState::request_.version_info` and `response_nonce` are updated in `onDiscoveryResponse()`; the version string is set from `message->version_info()`.\n   - Delta: `DeltaSubscriptionState::requested_resource_state_` (a map of resource name \u2192 `ResourceState` with per-resource version strings) is updated in `addResourceStateFromServer()`. Removed resources set state to `waitingForServer`. The nonce is carried in `UpdateAck` and inserted into the next request via `getNextRequestWithAck()`.\n   - xds_mux SotW: `SotwSubscriptionState::last_good_version_info_` and `last_good_nonce_` track accepted version.\n\n4. **Listener/Cluster Update Dispatch**:\n   - `GrpcMuxImpl::processDiscoveryResources()` / `WatchMap::onConfigUpdate()` dispatch decoded resources to registered `Watch` callbacks (`watch->callbacks_.onConfigUpdate()`).\n   - `GrpcSubscriptionImpl::onConfigUpdate()` is a thin adapter that records stats and forwards to the user-registered `SubscriptionCallbacks`.\n   - **LDS**: `LdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate()` calls `listener_manager_.addOrUpdateListener()` / `removeListener()` and pauses RDS/SDS during the update.\n   - **CDS**: `CdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate()` \u2192 `CdsApiHelper::onConfigUpdate()` calls `cm_.addOrUpdateCluster()` / `removeCluster()` while pausing EDS/LEDS/SDS.",
